Lorraine Cobourn cannot even handle bananas after being hit by a yellow taxi in Derby in May last year . 
  The 51-year-old had to leave her job as a Barclays bank clerk after she suffered a broken hip . 
  She has received two payouts and is now undergoing counselling to deal with the psychological damage she received . 
  She was struck by one of Derby's distinctive yellow Hackney Carriages in the city centre . 
  The taxi driver left the scene without helping her . 
  Ms Cobourn said she has a terrible fear of anything yellow . 
 